evidence: The preparation of the equimolar TiZrHfNbTa high-entropy alloy is performed with arc-melting and high-frequency induction melting techniques.
After stabilization up to  P ≈ 11%, the work hardening decreases for higher strains. The test was stopped at  P ≈ 17% corresponding to a total strain of 20% to avoid sample barreling.

In this paper, dislocation structures have been studied in a solid solution of a refractory Ti 20 Zr 20 Hf 20 Nb 20 Ta 20 HEA after mechanical tests and TEM observations. These observations allow the clarification of the deformation mechanisms at room temperature of the multi-component alloy.
